<br>
Mages, wizards and Druids (and bards) have some insane Rain AOE / PBAoE and AoE DD attack spells.  Clerics and Enchanters have some nice PBAoE and AOE Stun spells.<br>
<br>
In order to lay waste to a zone that can have a pain in the arse break in - specifically - Fear,  maximizing the firebpower of our finger wigglers can open up an aspect of the game that wasn't open to TF when we didn't have as much raw spell casting fury as is available now.<br>
<br>
RL Serano<br>
Time 10 PM EST<br>
Date 11 July 03 - alt day / do over day 18 July 02<br>
Location: Skyfire mountains north of OT zone in. <br>
Channel: TFAOE - mostly for organization once we start - rsay<br>
Goal to work on PBAoE / AOE DD/Rain / Stun techniques<br>
<br>
Side benifit - maybe get some pearl shards to drop for pre epic clerics.<br>
<br>
One negative here - the mobs in skyfire are notoriously Fire resistant.  Something not shared by our friends in fear.  This will limit the effectivness of some of the attacks.  After giving it a go in skyfire - we might move to Grey and try some of this out by SSRA temple area.  Tougher mobs but less fire resistsant.<br>
<br>
Yes - this idea was proposed by Cady - but was ill attended.  This time I would like to see EVERY mage/ Wizard / Druid Bard / cleric / chanter that can be online - try to make it down to Skyfire to rehearse this.  Specifically if you can make the Fear raid.  <br>
<br>
Please sign up on this thread - applicants are welcome to attend.<br>
<br>
